# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# NewsIntel — Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# Never commit .env to version control.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Application ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ENV=development          # development | production
DEBUG=true               # Set false in production

# ── Security (REQUIRED — must set before first run) ───────────────────────────
# Generate a strong key:
#   python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
SECRET_KEY=CHANGE_THIS_GENERATE_WITH_SECRETS_TOKEN_HEX_32

# JWT token lifetimes
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS=7

# CORS — comma-separated list of allowed frontend origins.
# Use * for local dev only. In production set your actual domain(s):
#   ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-app.up.railway.app,https://yourdomain.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*

# Authentication mode
#   required — /insights, /recommendations, /facts, /admin all require a valid JWT
#   optional — endpoints work without auth but unlock extra features when authenticated
#   disabled — no authentication enforced (local dev / testing only)
AUTH_MODE=required

# First-run admin account (created on startup if no users exist).
# Remove these from .env after your first login.
INITIAL_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
INITIAL_ADMIN_PASSWORD=ChangeMe123!

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SQLite (local dev — no setup required):
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./news_intel.db

# PostgreSQL (production):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname

# ── News API Keys (all optional — RSS feeds work without any keys) ─────────────
# Get free keys from:
#   NewsAPI:  https://newsapi.org/register         (100 req/day free)
#   Guardian: https://open-platform.theguardian.com (free)
#   GNews:    https://gnews.io/register            (100 req/day free)
NEWSAPI_KEY=
GUARDIAN_API_KEY=
GNEWS_API_KEY=

# ── Scheduler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FETCH_INTERVAL_MINUTES=30         # How often to fetch news (minutes)
MAX_ARTICLES_PER_SOURCE=30        # Max articles fetched per RSS feed per cycle
STOCK_UPDATE_INTERVAL_MINUTES=15  # How often to refresh market data

# ── Regional Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default region for /stocks endpoint
USER_REGION=global

# Active RSS feed regions (reduces ingestion load if you only need some)
# Comma-separated: global,west,europe,middle_east,india,southeast_asia,east_asia,africa,latin_america
# Leave empty to enable all regions
# ENABLED_REGIONS=global,west,europe,middle_east

# ── Rate Limiting ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are overridden per-tier by TieredRateLimitMiddleware in main.py.
# Changing RATE_LIMIT_DEFAULT here does not affect tiered limits — edit main.py.
RATE_LIMIT_DEFAULT=60
RATE_LIMIT_EXPENSIVE=20
RATE_LIMIT_ADMIN=10
RATE_LIMIT_STOCKS=30

# ── NLP ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SPACY_MODEL=en_core_web_sm   # Requires: python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm
MIN_ARTICLE_WORDS=50         # Articles shorter than this are discarded

# ── Trending ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TRENDING_WINDOW_HOURS=24
TRENDING_TOP_N=10
